  "body": "Port of https://github.com/dsgibbons/shap/issues/42\r\n\r\nUnit tests currently take ~20 mins to complete. If we could reduce that it could help reduce the time it takes to validate PRs, improving our effectiveness as reviewers.\r\n\r\nThe pytest logs show the names of the lowest 20 tests, which is a good way to prioritise tests to improve. \r\n\r\n## TODO\r\n\r\n- [ ] (Ongoing) refactor the slowest tests to run faster\r\n- [x] Cache the installation of the dependencies, which currently take several minutes from each test job.\r\n- [x] Investigate parallelising the tests to run on multiple CPUs.\r\n  - WIP attempt abandoned as it seems to actually make the tests run even slower!\r\n- [x] Get CodeCov working, to help us evaluate relevant test coverage when reviewing PRs.\r\n",
